# Public repo: track only README.md, LICENSE, core/, and plugin/.
# Everything else (docs/, CLAUDE.md, .claude/, etc.) stays local — never pushed
# to the Daedalus-AI-Forge repo.

# 1) Ignore everything at the repo root...
/*

# 2) ...except these (whitelist; contents of the folders are tracked):
!/.gitignore
!/README.md
!/LICENSE
!/core/
!/plugin/
!/.claude-plugin/

# 3) Keep Claude project files and docs local, even inside tracked dirs.
CLAUDE.md
.claude/
docs/

# 4) Never commit build / venv / cache junk inside the tracked dirs.
**/venv/
**/.venv/
**/__pycache__/
**/*.py[cod]
**/*.egg-info/
**/dist/
!plugin/dist/
!plugin/dist/**
**/build/
**/node_modules/
.DS_Store

# 5) Secrets & local-only runtime files.
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example
**/*.pem
**/*.key
**/*.sqlite
**/*.sqlite3
**/*.db
